definitions.definition: An alkaloid with the chemical formula C 20 H 24 N 2 O 2 , originally derived from cinchona bark (from plants of the genus Cinchona ), used to treat malaria and as an ingredient of tonic water , which presents as a bitter colourless powder ; also, a drug containing quinine or a chemical compound derived from it.

main_definition: ( pharmacology ) An alkaloid with the chemical formula C 20 H 24 N 2 O 2 , originally derived from cinchona bark (from plants of the genus Cinchona ), used to treat malaria and as an ingredient of tonic water , which presents as a bitter colourless powder ; also, a drug containing quinine or a chemical compound derived from it. [from early 19th c.]
